  {
    "id": 102,
    "post_url": "https://t.me/ClashReport/78859",
    "text": "Just hours before Trump’s deadline to launch massive strikes, Iran’s Supreme Leader Mojtaba Khamenei instructed negotiators to move toward a deal for the first time since the war began. An Israeli official, a regional official, and another source confirmed the shift. Two sources described Khamenei’s approval as: “A breakthrough.” A regional source added: “Without his green light, there wouldn’t have been a deal.” Due to assassination threats, Khamenei was communicating via handwritten notes carried by runners. He was personally involved in decisions Monday and Tuesday. Araghchi (Iran’s FM) pushed both the negotiations and Revolutionary Guard commanders toward accepting the deal. Source: Axios",
    "text_zh": null,
    "text_en": null,
